# Committing Changes to a Branch in Azure Repos

1. **Create a Branch:**
   ```bash
   git checkout -b your-branch-name
Replace your-branch-name with the desired branch name.

Make Changes:
Make the necessary changes to your code or files.

Add Changes to Staging:

bash
Copy code
git add .
Stage all changes. Replace . with specific file names if needed.

Commit Changes:

bash
Copy code
git commit -m "Your commit message here"
Replace "Your commit message here" with a meaningful message.

Push Changes to Azure Repos:

bash
Copy code
git push origin your-branch-name
Push changes to the remote repository.

Create a Pull Request (Optional):
If working in a shared repository:

Go to Azure DevOps repository.
Click "Pull Requests."
Click "New pull request."
Select source and target branches.
Review changes and create the pull request.
Now your changes are committed to the branch in Azure Repos. If a pull request was created, it can be reviewed and merged.
